# Widget Design Rules

## Size Limits
- Max ~300 lines per widget file
- Extract sub-widgets for complex build() methods
- One widget per file (private helpers OK)

## Composition
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Use ConsumerWidget for Riverpod-connected widgets
- Use StatelessWidget when no state or refs needed
- Use StatefulWidget only for animation controllers, focus nodes, text controllers

## Required States
Every data-driven widget MUST handle:
- Loading state (skeleton or spinner)
- Error state (user-friendly message + retry action)
- Empty state (helpful message)
- Data state (primary content)

## Accessibility
- Semantics widget for custom interactive components
- Minimum 48x48 touch targets
- Semantic labels on all icons and images
- Support text scaling (no fixed font sizes)
